Gloucester County was named after County Gloucester , England.

Gloucester County, New South Wales was one of the original Nineteen Counties in New South Wales , and is now one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It included the area around Port Stephens . It is bounded on the north and west by the Manning River , and on the south-west by the Williams River.
